  <prefix>Chapter</prefix>
  <num>23</num>
  <heading>Serious Illness or Injury of Inmate</heading>
  <section>
    <prefix>Regulation</prefix>
    <num>.01</num>
    <heading>Procedure.</heading>
    <para>
      <num>A.</num>
      <text>The institution shift commander or designee shall immediately notify the following officials when an inmate is seriously ill or injured:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(1)</num>
        <text>Commissioner or duty officer, as appropriate;</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(2)</num>
        <text>Warden; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(3)</num>
        <text>Assistant warden.</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>B.</num>
      <text>Upon notification of serious illness or injury to an inmate, the warden or designee shall contact an inmate's next of kin and inform them of the inmate's condition.</text>
    </para>
    <annotations/>
  </section>
